Sentencas: A complete electrode polarization model of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) has been developed and utilized to analyze the performance of Ni-CGO anode deposited by spray pyrolysis.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis

Sentencas: The model integrated a macro model and a micro model to consider electrode microstructural parameters in overall cell behavior.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis

Sentencas: Three different microstructures were prepared by varying the processing conditions.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis

Sentencas: The model was capable of predicting the electrochemical performance of the different microstructural variations with discrepancy smaller than 10%.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis

Sentencas: It was found that the activation loss was most dominant of all three major voltage losses.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis

Sentencas: The decrease in particle size improved the anode performance due to the increase in triple phase boundary area.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis

Sentencas: The model also showed that optimal particle size decreased with increasing anode porosity.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis

Sentencas: Overall, the work contributed to the understanding of cell performance in relation to the anode electrode microstructure.
Titulo: Modeling of Ni-CGO anode in a solid oxide fuel cell deposited by spray pyrolysis
